<br>
Well Xizor... couple of comments.<br>
<br>
1st regarding the numbers issue.  I for one would never tell anyone to let their guild &quot;stagnate.&quot; I do personally think a guild needs a certain base size in order to be healthy for the long term.  Probably somewhere around 15 to 20 people online at once during peak hours most days of the week is optimal.  However once this number is achieved I think a guild would be well advised to be slow on its invitations as much beyond that and you begin running into cases where people stop knowing everyone else in the guild and its harder to keep bad apples out.  I just tossed out the number of 50 members as my best guess as to what point in total membership you would start exceeding this friendly, everyone knows everyone size.  But needless to say its not a hard and fast rule.<br>
<br>
2nd comment... I noticed your general message boards are password protected.  I certainly don't mind you keeping official officer business out of the public eye, but I do like wandering into the main boards of prospective members just to get a feel for what sort of chit chat goes on amoung their members. Heh... plus I like to offer my 2cp and advice to make myself sound knowledgeable and important. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In any case, thanks for expressing an interest.  /wave<br>
