</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5DBE6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/uxizorpathfinder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xizor Pathfinder</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#B76D00>(9/4/01 9:56:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Menacing Horde</span><hr size=1> Ahh Mukhtar my friend, hello. I was wondering what roll you play in the Coalition, and it seems you play a large one. On that note we are wondering... what is the structure of this Coalition? Is it a true Senate type atmosphere? Or is there one Guild or even Person handling the majority of the issues and decisions regarding Coalition affairs? A Chairperson or Chairguild so to speak? And if their is a &quot;Chair&quot; is that a voted on position, and does it have term limits? <br>
<br>
As for your answer to question of guild size. Thank you. We have maintained a very open and family atmosphere in the Horde because right from the get go potential members will know what we are all about and if we or they feel that this is not a suitable situation for them .. well then it is time to say thank you and good luck on your travels. We are very social with each other no matter the level of exp. <br>
<br>
Ok now for your second comment. We have password protected our Guild Chat area from public view for a variety of reasons. Of which I will try to give you the ones of most importance to us. <br>
1- It gives our general populace a place to express concerns of how the guild is operating and vocalize any issues they may have. <br>
2- Also enables free discusion of other Guilds or even Players which may be positive or negative. And there is an open forum to discuss without fear of retribution from outside the family on any comments that are made.<br>
3- And most importantly, which also relates to first two, is that it creates an area where there is privacy for the main body. Our Warlord Consortium and our Captain's Log have the benefit of a forum where discusions can be had without concern of prying eyes or worry of misunderstanding a topic before it has come to resolution. And we felt our main body should have the same courtesy to be able to express themselves in.<br>
<br>
However there are still areas where you can view the 'interactions&quot; of our family and post any comments you may have as well. And these things are open to all. They are :<br>
Quests<br>
Events<br>
PvP Server<br>
Guest log<br>
Tech Center<br>
<br>
There are some good stories and interactions in the events and quests areas. And I have made it a point to all to be sure to post there Topics in an &quot;appropriate&quot; area. So all can share in our adventures. <br>
<br>
I hope this clears things up for you concerning our practices.  <p>Strength and Honor!!<BR>
<BR>
Warlord<BR>
Xizor Pathfinder<BR>
 <BR>
Noble Roaming Ranger</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E4E9EF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/umukhtaribnasim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mukhtar Ibn Asim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gatekeeper</span><br>  Posts: 187<br> <font color=#B76D00>(9/4/01 12:01:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Menacing Horde</span><hr size=1> Our charter which lays out how the LCG is governed can be found at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthelanyscoalitionofguildsfrm4.showMessage?topicID=2.topic">pub66.ezboard.com/fthelan...ID=2.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
As implied in the charter all member guilds have two primary council representatives.  There are provisions for alternate representatives for tie breaking votes, and voting when one of the primary council members is away and unable to take part in a discussion, but thus far none of us have designated alternate representatives yet.<br>
<br>
As to my own role, I am one of the council representatives from the Guardians of Dawn along with Kelyna.  I also am one of the more active event organizers in the LCG, and primary author of LCG's charter.  /shrug  I try not to act too dictatorish. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Not official stuff... setting up events for instance, can be done by anyone.  Day to day affairs are by and large just allowed to happen without council oversight.  The only time when the LCG council will step in is when there is a problem that exists that the involved guilds are not addressing, and when there are decisions to be made regarding changes to the LCG charter, or to LCG membership status of existing member guilds or new applicants.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Mukhtar Ibn Asim Farseeker<br>
Suicidal tanking Illusionist of the 52nd blow to the head<br>
Co-leader Guardians of Dawn<br>
Lants Coalition of Guilds Council Member<br>
